<div class="non_toggle_area" id="comment-3571166">
  <div class="non_toggle_label">
       <span class="scomments_info">Thu, 05/16/2013 - 19:55 | <a href="/news/2013-05-16/visualizing-great-gold-rout#comment-3571166" class="active">3571166</a></span>
              <b><a href="/users/antifederalist" title="View user profile.">Antifederalist</a></b>
  </div>

  <div class="comment-content">
    <div class="author"><div class="picture">
  <a href="/users/antifederalist" title="View user profile."><img src="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/pictures/picture-11428.jpg" alt="Antifederalist&#039;s picture" title="Antifederalist&#039;s picture"  /></a></div>
</div><div class="author"></div>
    <p>Squeeky:</p>
<p>You are so wrong in so many ways it is hard to know where to start.</p>
<p>Gold and fiat currency are substitutes, and opposites.  You can always exchange one for the other.</p>
<p>They both have one of the characteristics of money, they can be used for transactions.  However,  only one is a long term store of value and cannot be debased.</p>
<p>The value of gold never changes.  The value of paper money, not so much.</p>
<p>So these price changes you allude to in gold are really just valuation changes in the value of paper.  </p>
<p>The value of gold as measured in dollars will one day be infinite.</p>
<p>Get it?</p>

